HEADWORD: manila bean
<hw>manila bean</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tuberous-rooted twining annual
vine (<spn>Psophocarpus tetragonolobus</spn>) bearing clusters of
purplish flowers and pods with four jagged wings; Old World
tropics.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> winged bean, winged pea, goa bean, goa bean vine,
<spn>Psophocarpus tetragonolobus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manila grass</ent>⟦br⟧
